DISEASE: Mitochondrial Complex I Deficiency, Nuclear Type 12
RECORD:
Rare disease patients have complex clinical representations. Patients with Mitochondrial Complex I Deficiency, Nuclear Type 12 present clinical features that include a broad spectrum of severity, from neonatal onset to adult onset, and a wide range of organ involvement.

The aim of this study was to describe the clinical features of patients with Mitochondrial Complex I Deficiency, Nuclear Type 12 and to identify the most common clinical patterns.
